@node USSAGE_CLI "Ussage_CLI"

The CLI-Version of KSW-FILEWORKS ('KSW-FW_CLIv10a.exe') can copy/rename one
choosen file/filename.


KSW-FW_CLIv10a.exe  SETTINGSPATH+FILE  COPY/RENAME  SOURCEPATH+FILE  DESTINATIONPATH


SETTINGSPATH+FILE  :   settingsfile saved with KSW-FILEWORKS (the GUI-Version)
                       that will set the changings for the filename

COPY/RENAME        :   copy for copying a file
                       rename for renameing a file

SOURCEPATH+FILE    :   the file for copying or renameing

DESTINATIONPATH    :   enter it only if you want to copy a file!
                       the destinationpath for copying

@endnode




@node REQ "Reqirements"


KSW-FILEWORKS requires at last:

an AMIGA with 68020 CPU
(but it's written in Blitz2 and maybe slow on slow CPU's)
Kickstart v2 or higher
Workbench v2 or higher



KSW-FILEWORKS is testet and coded on the following AMIGA-system:


AMIGA 1200 HD
CPU 68030 28MHz + FPU
Kickstart v3 (40.68)
Workbench v3 (40.42)

coded in Blitz2 (v2.1)


@endnode
@node MAINWIN "MAIN window"

LOAD SETTINGS             :   load settings

SAVE SETTINGS             :   save settings

CHECKBOX CHANGE CHARS     :   switch on/off the changing of single letters
                              by copying/renameing

STRINGBOX CHANGE CHARS    :   here you can enter the single letters
                              that will be changed by copying/renameing,
                              first enter the letter that must be changed,
                              then enter '=' followed by the letter
                              for the letter-replacement.
                              if you enter more then one replacements (max.256)
                              enter a space after the first
                              replacement-setting.
                              example: ' Ä=AE Ö=OE .=.. .=.. '

CHECKBOX CHANGE INDEX     :   switch on/off the adding/changing of the
                              filenames index

STRINGBOX CHANGE INDEX    :   here you can enter the index
                              that will be added changed by copying/renameing.
                              don't forget the '.'!
                              example: '.TXT'

CHECKBOX FILENAME LENGTH  :   switch on/off the cutting of the
                              filename

NUMBBOX FILENAME LENGTH   :   here you can enter filename-length
                              that will be used by copying/renameing.
                              example: '8'

RENAME                    :   rename files

COPY                      :   copy files


@endnode



@node HTU "How to use"

* first enter and set your several changings for copying or renaming.

* choose copy/rename

* select files by using the requester (pressing SHIFT for multiselect!)

* choose a destination path by using the requester (not by renameing)

-----------------

* pressing SHIFT in progress for slow-down the progress-speed

* pressing CTRL+C in progress for don't copy/rename the file


@endnode



@node HIW "How it works"

KSW-FILEWORKS copys or renames several files that could be choosen by
file-requesters.


Is copying or renameing in progress, KSW-FILEWORKS can change the filename:

It can convert a single letter of the filename into another!
(Ä -> AE)

It can add or rename the (last) index of an file!
(dummy.TXT -> dummy.BAK)

It can cut the filename by choosing the number of filename letters!
(good_morning.TXT -> good_mor.TXT)

@endnode



