@node INST "Installation / Execution"


Installation:

Copy the drawer 'KSW-FILEWORKS' to your choosen path or disk.




Start:

Click on the 'KSW-FWv10b_ur.exe'-Icon.


@endnode
@node WHAT "What it is!"

KSW-FILEWORKS is a copy/rename-tool with his own gui that brings the
possibility to change the filename of an file by setting several options.

So you can shorten the filename of a file, you can change different letters in
your filename or you can add or change the index of a file.

I use the tool for transfering my text-files to a MS-DOS-disk.
I use an old cross-dos-version with only 8 letters per filename + index.
So i need it to shorten my filenames intelligent and automatically
and i need to change some german letters into compatible ones.

For example KSW-FILEWORKS can do this changings by copying or renameing:

SOURCE-FILE:                  DESTINATION-FILE:

"ähnlichkeiten.amk.text"      "aehnlich.TXT"


-------------------------------------------

Have fun, Alexander M. Korn

@endnode

